Package com.im.njams.sdk.communication

Class NjamsSender

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.im.njams.sdk.communication.NjamsSender
  • public class NjamsSender
extends Object
    This class enforces the maxQueueLength setting. It uses the maxQueueLengthHandler to enforce the discardPolicy, if the maxQueueLength is exceeded all message sending is funneled through this class, which creates and uses a pool of senders to multi-thread message sending
    Version:
    4.0.6
    Author:
    hsiegeln

    • Method Detail

      • takeSharedSender

        public static NjamsSender takeSharedSender​(Settings settings)
        Returns the one shared sender instance. On first access, the instance is lazily created. All later access will get the same instance until the instance has closed. Then a new instance is created if required. Calling this method tracks usage of the sender instance. I.e., after taking a sender, it must be Sender.close()d to return the instance and allow the implementation to keep track of usage. Calling Sender.close() does not really close the actual sender as long as it is still being used. Only when it is no longer used (close has been called as often as it has been taken), the real sender instance will be closed finally.
        Parameters:
        settings - Only used if a new instance needs to be created.
        Returns:
        The shared sender instance as explained above.

      • close

        public void close()
        This method closes the ThreadPoolExecutor safely. It awaits the termination for 10 seconds, after that, an InterruptedException will be thrown and the senders will be closed.
